Description: Videogames pioneer creating 'hybrid games', bringing the best of games and TV together into a unique interactive entertainment experience.
Headquarters Regions: Nordic Countries, Scandinavia, Europe, Middle East, and Africa (EMEA)
Full Description: PortalOne is a pioneering startup in the videogames industry, taking the best parts of games and the best parts of TV and merging them together to create an immersive entertainment experience unlike anything that's been seen before. PortalOne's business model is centered around the concept of 'hybrid games', a novel category that combines elements of traditional gaming with interactive TV shows. Currently accessible only via mobile devices, the company hosts daily 24-hour tournaments every day where players can compete in a variety of games across different genres, including Atari games, for which the company has the exclusive global distribution rights for many of its titles like 'Pong', 'Breakout' and 'Centipede'. These games are not just standalone experiences, but are integrated with TV shows broadcasted within the games themselves. Players play throughout the day with the goal of climbing the Leaderboards for each game, with the opportunity to win real prizes such as cash and holidays. PortalOne's first show format, the 'Arcade Show' -- the TV component of hybrid games -- is hosted every single day in the PortalOne app. The show sees special guests come into the PortalOne universe and become immersed inside the game worlds as real characters. They play a round of a PortalOne game, and then players play against them on their mobile device at home. Previous guests on the Arcade Show include Justin Bieber, Demi Lovato, Tori Kelly, and Atari founder Nolan Bushnell.  The company has been operational since 2018 and has been steadfast in its mission to merge the best aspects of the gaming and TV industries. PortalOne's vision is to be the ultimate destination for hybrid games, in the same way that Spotify is for music and podcasts, and Netflix is for TV and film. PortalOne will host hundreds of games across all genres on its platform, with multiple show formats in its universe. The company also intends to become cross-platform. Currently operating in the US & Canada and Norway, PortalOne aims to be available worldwide with studios around the world producing localized TV shows for different geographies.
Industry Groups: Gaming, Media and Entertainment, Video
Founders: Bård Anders Kasin, Stig Olav Kasin
Top 5 Investors: Temasek Holdings, Founders Fund, Coatue, Tiger Global Management, TQ Ventures

Description: Digital Health, AI, Video Analysis, Medical Device, SaaS, Computer Vision,
Headquarters Regions: Nordic Countries, Scandinavia, Europe, Middle East, and Africa (EMEA)
Full Description: Colorectal cancer (CRC) is one of the most prevalent cancer forms with close to 2 million new cases per year worldwide. Each year approximately 800.000 patients die of their CRC. The gold standard for diagnosis of CRC is colonoscopy, targeting polyps, abnormal tissue growths that may evolve into cancer. Early disease detection has a significant impact on mortality from colorectal cancer, going from a high 5-year survival probability of 90% if detected early, to a low 10-30% 5-year survival probability in later stages. Studies have shown that up to 40% of polyps can be missed during colonoscopies. Large variations in detection rates are also observed between physicians.  To remedy the variability in detection rates, there is a high medical need for tools to improve detection of polyps in colonoscopy. Such tools can save lives and reduce the treatment costs for hospitals and society by preventing CRC cases due to early detection. Based on more than 10 years of research conducted at Simula Research Laboratory, we are developing, documenting and commercializing an AI-powered digital health system that can detect polyps in real-time during a colonoscopy examination without interruption of the procedure. The device is connected to the video output of standard endoscopy equipment and provides feedback on visible lesions to the performing doctor overlaid on their examination screen. Augere's vision is to harness the currently untapped potential of endoscopic video and augment the information by analyzing it using Augere's best-in-class technology. This opens a whole new range of valuable services of patient-adapted healthcare that has the potential to transform the field of endoscopy.
Industry Groups: Artificial Intelligence (AI), Data and Analytics, Hardware, Health Care, Science and Engineering, Software

Full Description: Nordic Nanovector is a biopharmaceutical company dedicated to extending and improving the lives of patients with haematological cancers through the development and commercialisation of innovative targeted therapeutics. The company's lead clinical-stage product is Betalutin®, the first in a new class of antibody radionuclide conjugates (ARCs), designed to improve upon and complement current options for the treatment of non-Hodgkin lymphoma (NHL). NHL is an indication with substantial unmet medical need and orphan drug opportunities. Betalutin® is a tumour-seeking anti-CD37 antibody conjugated to a low-intensity radionuclide (lutetium-177). It is showing promising efficacy and tolerability in a Phase 1/2 clinical study in a difficult-to-treat NHL patient population. The company aims to develop Betalutin® for the treatment of patients with relapsed/refractory NHL. Nordic Nanovector intends to retain marketing rights and to actively participate in the commercialisation of Betalutin® in core markets, while exploring potential distribution agreements in selected geographies. Nordic Nanovector is committed to building a pipeline of novel ARCs and antibody drug conjugates (ADCs) addressing multiple selected haematological malignancies based on proprietary technologies and expertise, and with technologies from partners where complementary.

Description: We're passionate about financial inclusion. We make a borderless credit scoring, fair risk profiles, and a portable financial history
Headquarters Regions: Nordic Countries, Scandinavia, Europe, Middle East, and Africa (EMEA)
Full Description: At goscore, we're passionate about financial inclusion. We achieve this through cross-border credit scoring, fair risk profiles, and a portable financial history that moves from country to country with you.  Historically, people have been excluded from financial services because of, let's say, poverty. While you don’t have a proper risk profile, you fall prey to payday lenders. Now you are trapped. Others have chosen to exclude themselves from traditional financial services. What that means? They make lifestyle decisions to become nomadic in the way they live, work, and earn money. The challenge that entrepreneurs and nomads have is that they can't get an affordable rental apartment, or a mobile phone, or a credit card in their new home. Why? For people with both these profiles, either their credit history is not portable or a standard risk profile simply doesn't suit them. So at goscore we built a cross-border credit scoring solution that is fair and human-centric. We bring your financial history with you wherever you go.  Goscore also enables lenders to accurately assess your creditworthiness based on up-to-date information from various data sources. goscore brings your credit history to you, without borders. So, whoever was previously excluded, is now included. Using machine learning, our solution leverages up-to-date transactional data and derives relevant financial insights to build real-time comprehensive financial profiles. In turn, these profiles enable our customers to make sustainable lending decisions. Our technology recently helped a lender to increase creditworthy borrowers by 21% and reduce default rates by 32%. We are an authorized credit scoring company in Norway.
Industry Groups: Financial Services, Software
Founders: Alex Shub, Anastasiya Lebedz, Kris Kalbasiuk, Maksim Hardziyenak

Our initial target market, the day cruiser, is ripe for innovation.
